g.text: Meetups start back up again. Our group is growing and bustin’ at the seams.
Nerdy Girls launches its first all girls FTC robotics team! Ain’t no party like a prototyping party.
Nerdy Girls FTC is sprinting to bring a new robot to life.
Crankin’ out a robot for our first competition in 2 weeks. We’ve gotta teach ourselves Java so we can code this lil son of a biscuit.
We need more space! Nerdy Girls moves to a secret location: the Robot Workshop.
“Teen Girls are Plotting Secret Takeover of Robotics World” article published on GirlPowered’s blog.
Nerdy Girls crash the local FRC team to work on the big 100 lbs. bots.
The State Championship! We go out in a fiery blaze of glory.
“Nerdy Girls: Underground Robotics Society” video by FIRST WA.
It’s not over yet. Time for Nerdy Girls to battle the big bots at local FRC competitions.
“20 Inspiring Women (and Girls) Changing the World of Robotics” article published on Ozobot’s blog.
The Friday night robot building parties keep on rolling.
Our members are hungry and moving fast. It’s an all out sprint to stay ahead of them with our tutorials.
Nerdy Girls Documentary premieres at the Seattle International Film Festival. Sometimes really cool things happen to ordinary nerds.
Nerdy Girls Documentary (2018) by Graham Bourque.
These nocturnal nerds come out into the daylight to bring robot magic to Ellensburg School District’s Summer Literacy Camp.
We’re insanely honored that the Seattle Seahawks and Boeing selected Nerdy Girls to be a Legion of Youth - Powered by Boeing organization. (Photo courtesy of Seattle Seahawks.)

In this episode, a Nerdy Girls competitive robot assists the Seattle Seahawks at Training Camp, thereby fulfilling its deepest robot dreams. Watch the video here. (Photo courtesy of Seattle Seahawks.)
Meetups start back up again. Season 3, here we gooo.
The Kurt Giessler Foundation funds the purchase of an all-new arsenal of laptops!
A new FTC season begins! But this time, Nerdy Girls is powering two teams: the Plastic Avocado Cult and the Flaming Hippogriffs.
Our two FTC teams launch into their first competition of the season!
The Plastic Avocado Cult and the Flaming Hippogriffs crush it at the FTC Interleague competition and qualify for the State Championship!
Our FTC robots are revealed, in their full majesty. Double trouble.
“Referee Finds Inspiration in Rural, All-Girls Robotics Program” article written by Rob Fyfe for FIRST’s blog.
“The Nerdy Girls of Ellensburg are building robots to dismantle the patriarchy” article written by Dorothy Edwards for Crosscut. (Photo courtesy of Dorothy Edwards.)
Congresswoman Kim Schrier visits the Robot Workshop!
Nerdy Girls hosts Botquest, a summer camp for local cool kids.
We get to hang out with Senator Patty Murray at the Robot Workshop!
Benaroya Research Institute donates two medical robots to Nerdy Girls! Wowza!
Our first ever coding workshop at the Ellensburg Public Library. These teens are learning epic-gamer text-based code: ROBOTC.
Scrambling to conquer robot battles before summer break.
Say what?? Nerdy Girls receives a grant from the Suncadia Fund for Community Enhancement for advanced robot kits.

g.text: Boom goes the dynamite. Nerdy Girls is brought forth into the world. Behold our first meetup.
Our lives change when we join our small town’s FRC team. But we can’t help but ask....wh-why are we so alone? :’(
Birthing our first crowdfunding campaign and thus leaping into the unknown.
Our first robot kits land! Things are heating up.
Scrounging up laptops from all corners of the community.
A crazy, newfangled idea is born. The planning and prototyping begins.
We release a sneak peek of our brand new robotics system: Spicy Meatbots. (Now that’s a spicy meat-a-bot!)
After crushing it hard with our two robots, our FTC season wraps up. What a rush!
During our very first remote hackathon, Nerdy Girls members Tessa and Aislin bring the Senate Stalker: Climate Edition™ to life. :O
Nerdy Girls members become Beta Testers, where they are the very first to test out Spicy Meatbot kits!
Our work commences on our insane new curriculum: The Robot Underground.
Though the 2020 pandemic turned everything on its head for us and our members, it ended up being the impetus for us to radically reimagine what Nerdy Girls could be. Check out our Master Plan.
